A negotiation game where players are taking up spaces along many intersecting tracks. On a players turn, a player can place a worker on the lowest track if able, move a worker along a path if its full and a major of all players in that region, or move caesar (allows players to move without negotiation).
An excellent negotiation game. The recent reimplementation (Zoo Vadis) lloks interesting, but I am a big fan of the pure negotiation of the original.

Amazing with the right group, the rules get out of the way very quickly and before you know it you're arguing and scheming with the rest of the table. I like this version, but I'm curious to try Zoo Vadis as I think I'd find that easier to get to the table.
The best negotiation game I've played to date.
